Sentencas: This study reports the successful preparation of potential candidate Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) oxides for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) by a combined citrate-ethylenediaminete-traacetic acid (EDTA) complexing method.
Titulo: Effect of pH value on the synthesis and characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ powders prepared by the citrate-EDTA complexing method

Sentencas: The resulting crystal properties, chemical composition, conductivity, and electrochemical properties were studied by X-ray diffraction (XRD), inductively coupled plasma mass spectroscopy (ICP-MS), energy dispersive spectrum (EDS), four-point DC measurement and AC impedance.
Titulo: Effect of pH value on the synthesis and characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ powders prepared by the citrate-EDTA complexing method

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction results of all samples with different pH values reveal a basic perovskite structure.
Titulo: Effect of pH value on the synthesis and characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ powders prepared by the citrate-EDTA complexing method

Sentencas: Although samples prepared from different pH solutions have a similar structure, their chemical composition and grain morphologies are different.
Titulo: Effect of pH value on the synthesis and characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ powders prepared by the citrate-EDTA complexing method

Sentencas: The optimized composition of BSCF is the sample prepared from the precursor solution with a pH value of 6; this produced highest conductivity at 50.2 S/cm at 400 degrees C, which is 1.3 times higher than the sample prepared from the precursor solution with a pH value of 9.
Titulo: Effect of pH value on the synthesis and characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ powders prepared by the citrate-EDTA complexing method

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectra at an intermediate temperature reveal the better electrochemical performance of BSCF electrode prepared from the solution with pH of 6.
Titulo: Effect of pH value on the synthesis and characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ powders prepared by the citrate-EDTA complexing method

Sentencas: The lowest polarization resistance values for charge transfer and oxygen diffusion are 0.07 and 0.11 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of pH value on the synthesis and characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ powders prepared by the citrate-EDTA complexing method
